A brain-damaged man accused of starting a 1996 fire at an Ohio fireworks store that killed nine people died earlier this month at a mental health facility.

Todd Hall died March 8 in Athens where he had been getting treatment for the last several years, according to the Lawrence County Prosecutor's Office.

A cause of death for the 43-year-old couldn't be immediately confirmed Monday. 

