Hall, of Proctorville, was 24 when prosecutors say that, as a prank, he threw a lighted cigarette on a shelf crammed with fireworks at the Ohio River Fireworks store in Scottown, about 100 miles southeast of Cincinnati. 

The blaze on July 3, 1996, killed nine people and eleven people were injured.

Five of the victims were from Ohio; the four others were from nearby West Virginia.

